      "amount": "2 sprigs"
    },
    {
      "name": "flambe brandy",
      "amount": "2 tablespoons"
    },
    {
      "name": "sliced red onion",
      "amount": "1 large"
    },
    {
      "name": "chopped fresh parsley",
      "amount": "1/4 cup"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Season the lamb shanks with salt and pepper.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Sear the lamb shanks until browned, then set them aside.",
    "Add the sliced red onion to the pot and cook until softened.",
    "Add the barbecue sauce, brown sugar, flour, beef broth, red wine, and thyme to the pot.",
    "Return the lamb shanks to the pot and bring the mixture to a simmer.",
    "Transfer the pot to the preheated oven and cook for 20 minutes.",
    "Remove the pot from the oven and carefully flambe the mixture with the brandy.",
    "Return the pot to the oven and continue cooking for an additional 10-15 minutes.",
    "Remove the pot from the oven and let it cool slightly.",
    "Sprinkle the chopped parsley over the top of the lamb shanks and serve."
  ],
